condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Legal Arrangements for the Utility to Operate the Maputo Water Supply System | Description :The Utility tooperate the Greater Maputo Water Supply System shall be a Corporation under Mozambican law. The contract between FIPAG and theUtility shall guarantee the financial obligations of previous Financing Agreements and Credit Agreements of FIPAG, and thesustainability of the future investments in the system, by defining clearly the payments and obligations of each party | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Maintenance of Adequacy of Water Tariffs | Description :The tariffs for the systems under both the direct andindirect responsibility of FIPAG shall reflect the principles of full cost recovery and shall be sufficient to cover operatingexpenses, depreciation, the cost of capital, and, where applicable, lease fees to FIPAG in a reasonable time horizon for all saidsystems. These tariffs shall be assessed annually | Frequency :Yearly
